metadata.name: Torsion #128
metadata.description:
This project aims to explore the possibilities offered by the implementation of a simulation of slit-scanning or rolling-shutter.
A line runs through a 3D animation and freezes the pixels at its level. This results in a distortion effect giving the initial objects twisted and strange shapes.

Artist: Estienne

metadata.description:
Weaving on the astral plane. Lines of transmission. 
Some journeys are straightforward, others yield a multitude of pathways.
Disconnect to interpret.

(As an experiment) the rarity values assigned to this artwork are completely arbitrary, and are in no way connected to the visual output of the minted piece. One might wonder, why have rarity values at all? That's what I ask myself any time I see a value based on rarity attributes instead of viewer aesthetic. 

That being said, I suppose it's up to each person to decide for themselves the value of art...

This artwork was created using p5js.

metadata.name: hollow #152
metadata.description:
In 1993, Basque sculptor Eduardo Chillida proposed a project to create an immense void inside Tindaya, the Sacred Mountain of Fuerteventura's indigenous inhabitants. The hollow cube measuring approximately 45 x 50 x 65 meters was conceived as a space for "all the people" to "fully experience the tininess of humankind".

The idea of the project dates back to the 1980s, and it took the artist years of searching for the ideal mountain in different parts of the world. However, what was ideal for Chillida evoked a lot of controversy due to the environmental and social impact of the project. There was uncertainty about Tindaya's structural feasibility and the potential harm to the ancient petroglyphs engraved on its surface. What's more, the financial sustainability of the project's economic model would depend on hundreds of thousands of tourists visiting the site each year, converting a work of art into a holiday attraction.

Chillida called his project the Monument to Tolerance. Although it never came into existence, it has caused division and conflict since it was conceived.


"hollow" is an exploration of 256 voids in nonexistent natural monuments. Made of digital matter instead of stone and lacking cultural charge, its sole purpose is to contemplate the tininess of humankind.


-----

Click on the image to open the menu. You may choose the quality from preview to the resolution of a print of approximately 30cm in height. In live mode, click on PNG to save the rendered image.

Depending on the device and CPU usage, it takes from a few seconds (on fast computers) to a minute (sometimes more) on mid-tier phones to render the image. 

Requirements: 1GB of RAM. The system needs up to 200 MB of free RAM for rendering square preview images and up to 400 MB of free RAM for rendering square images at the highest resolution. I tested on Chrome, Safari, Firefox, Edge / Windows, Mac OS, Android, and iPhone, but please make sure it works on your device before minting.

-----

Possible features:

color scheme: cairngorm, alborz, bardenas, atlas, bieszczady, watkins

proportions: square, wide, standard, narrow

frame: none, vignette, bright, dark, bright with vignette, dark with vignette

visitors: tourists, tourists and birds, solitary flock of birds, only light

metadata.name: Alleles #126
metadata.description:
An allele, short for 'allelomorph', is an alternative version of a specific gene.

This collection (which is in no way scientifically accurate), was born out of an exercise in simplicity. Outputs are made up of arrangements of squares in various compositions, yet within that we are free to imagine what they could mean. For some, the resulting shapes might represent DNA strands or atoms. Others might see cells or the building blocks of the hereditary instructions that shape us as individuals. 

A generative genetic report accompanies each output to spark the imagination and attempt to attach further meaning to each composition. Some gene sequences carry mutations, however not all mutations are visually apparent. Please refer to the fxhash features to view the reports accordingly.

Texture is used subtly, so for maximum enjoyment it is recommended that you save and view your outputs at full size in order to best enjoy the details.

Press 'S' to save a 2400 x 3396 px PNG file.

attributes.name: Genetic Profile
attributes.value: Interpretation of the available genetic information suggests subject may posess with a high degree of certainty: infrequent periods of pessimism and lack of self-confidence, yet also displays a high degree of creativity and persistence. Maximum potential hereditary height (excluding nutritional and environmental factors) is estimated at 157-163cm. Projected natural lifespan estimated at 73-74 years.

metadata.name: Whirled Peas #41
metadata.description:
Help us spread ‚ÄúWhirled Peas!‚Äù

Whirled Peas is a never-before attempted take on NFT (Non Fungible Tokens), but unlike NFTs that have come before, this will be a collective effort to raise money for vulnerable Ukrainian women, LGBTQIA+ people, and disabled refugees who are displaced and endangered by the war as part of the GISH ‚ÄúChange A Life: Ukraine‚Äù charity initiative to benefit Legacy of War Foundation and Random Acts.

This collaborative art piece by Misha Collins and Shawn Kemp is being unleashed into the NFT community as part of GISH (the Greatest International Scavenger Hunt), which runs from July 30 - Aug 6. Minting is open to GISH participants only via rolling whitelist spots through August 6, 2022, but after minting, anyone can purchase a Whirled Peas NFT. After the GISH Hunt ends August 6, 2022 at 10 PM PDT, all additional editions will be burned and no additional art will be generated, so there will be limited numbers of this art piece available.

GISH participants will need the support of the fxhash community who understand how generative art works and who have a few tez(Íú©)  to donate to the cause, so if you want to help, please find a #WhirledPeas GISH player on social media, hook them up with a few tez(Íú©) and help them learn about minting on fxhash. 

100% of the mint and 25% of each secondary sale (the maximum portion allowable on the platform) goes to our charity initiative (minus gas and platform fees). Additionally, we ask that anyone collecting this NFT through the week of August 6 do so as a part of our charity campaign and, on your honor, promise to donate 100% of your profits to this charity initiative as well by transferring it to the charity wallet (tz2SBWGZn7mf4UxoPv6tD1HM3sVvFx2EWKtA). Then, re-list it to keep it circulating to help vulnerable Ukrainians ‚Äî kind of like a virtual game of hot potato, but with NFT art. After August 6, we welcome you to buy and sell it as you normally would, though we still hope you donate some or all of your profits to the cause. Of course, we can‚Äôt control what sellers down the chain choose to do, but we are grateful for your support of this charity initiative. Thank you for helping us to help Ukrainians.

Learn More - https://alleditions.art/p/whirled-peas

metadata.name: the Horizon #88
metadata.description:
I am interested in and pay attention to repeating patterns in nature. Searching for the possibility of depicting this rhythm, texture, and space opens this opportunity as a new experience for me. And how can I convert time to image? In this work, I have depicted the circle of wandering, like the sun that fluctuates in every horizon and climate, sometimes hot and tense and sometimes its rays like the morning breeze caressing our face, calling us to a new beginning. Where is your sun on the horizon, and what time is it in your world?
Made in p5js
Created July 2022
Artist: @ChistaAi
